                            <comment id="335036" author="adilger" created="Mon, 16 May 2022 22:31:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Likely still the same issue as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3127&quot; title=&quot;replay-single test_73b: fchmod: No such file or directory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3127&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3127&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  This subtest was disabled via that ticket, but re-enabled on 2017-10-16 by patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/27404&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/27404&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9590&quot; title=&quot;replay-single test cases 61d 89 73b remove from ALWAYS_EXCEPT&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9590&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9590&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: remove replay-single tests from ALWAYS_EXCEPT&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; likely because it doesn&apos;t fail very often.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems more  likely to hit on ZFS than ldiskfs, even  though these subtests are run the same number of times for each filesystem  type (AFAIK), so it is likely that the test is racy, and the slower ZFS performance opens up this race.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
